Portuguese Government Approves Budget Proposal for Next Year

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-10-13T22:30:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/portuguese-government-approves-budget-proposal-for-next-year.html
The  Portuguese government  approved
the budget proposal for 2012 and a proposal for an amendment to
the 2011 budget at a cabinet meeting today.  The cabinet also approved a law that will lessen the
increase in electricity prices in 2012, according to a statement
posted on the government’s website.  The budget proposal has to be discussed and voted in
parliament. The coalition government is backed by the  Social
Democrats  and the  People’s Party , which combined have a majority
of seats in the legislature.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jim Silver at 
 jsilver@bloomberg.net  